I"Ëy<p>I gave a talk for an online discussion group giving a summary of some of the things Iâ€™ve posted on this blog. The talk was on some of my experiences and opinions on category theory flavored things programmed for real computers with a focus on calculating answers rather than proving things. It was the Wednesday right after the election, kind of a nerve wracking time.</p>

<p>Rough Outline:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Language Choice. Haskell vs Theorem provers vs Python vs Julia</li>
  <li>Computer functions as categories.</li>
  <li>Linear operators as a category</li>
  <li>Automatic differentiation</li>
  <li>Relations</li>
  <li>Linear relations</li>
  <li>Optimization problems as a category</li>
</ul>

<p>These topics are discussed in much greater detail in blog posts, which are linked in the notes below.</p>

